I can remember a television ad for Degrassi where a homely girl gets giddy because a boy told her that she is "so much more than the smart one."
That ad tells you all you need to know about the series.  The ad campaigns are aimed at homely girls. Watch Degrassi and the guys will tell you exactly what you want to hear.  This is a feel-good show for pre-teen girls without a social life.  An instant social life inside your computer or your television.

What makes it worse is the emptiness of the stories.  After 10 seasons, the stories have become predictable.  Each episode begins with some lie that ends up being exposed.  You can almost set your watch by it.  It is apparent that the series is aimed at younger viewers that have not watched much television before and are susceptible to predictable plots.

Our culture has been addicted to television for decades.  But in recent years, the industry has set its sights on younger and younger audiences.  Today's children don't need a social life because one is provided for them on their electronic devices.  They provide a social life to the most vulnerable of the younger generation, those children don't try as hard to develop their own lives and the industry can peddle any idea it wants - men are women, up is down, day is night, etc.  There are long-term effects.  We become a society of Eloi, incapable of thinking for ourselves or even turning off the television.
This show is amazing. This was one of my favorite seasons. I recommend this show to anyone.

The packaging is a bit confusing: the discs don't have clear labelling, and although there are 4 discs in the set, they are not numbered. Looking for a specific episode? You have to search through each disc, and remember what order you place them in. This quibble aside, the set is worth having for collectors.
Awesome!

I love Degrassi still as it's going onto it's 14th or 15th season. I think season 11 has been one of my favorites so far. I really enjoy the cast and feel like they incorporated and focused on some really great issues that are going on in high schools everywhere today.
Degrassi deserves five stars for anything it does. As a Degrassi fan since I was 12, there is literally nothing this series can do to disappoint me.
